                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>The Secretary of State’s Panel of Consultants on Disarmament met at Cambridge,
                    Massachusetts, June 19–21. <persName corresp="#p_OPPENHEIMERJR1">J. Robert
                        Oppenheimer</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_JOHNSONJE1">Joseph E.
                        Johnson</persName>, and <persName corresp="#p_BUNDYMG1">McGeorge
                        Bundy</persName>, the Executive Secretary, were present throughout.
                        <persName corresp="#p_DICKEYJS1">John S. Dickey</persName> was present on
                    June 19 and 20. <persName corresp="#p_DULLESAW1">Allen W. Dulles</persName> and
                        <persName corresp="#p_BUSHDV1">Vannevar Bush</persName> were unable to
                    participate. The meetings were held mainly for the purpose of discussing general
                    aspects of the question of disarmament with a number of visiting experts. No
                    conclusions were formally recorded. Ten pages of minutes of the sessions,
                    prepared by <persName corresp="#p_BUNDYMG1">Bundy</persName>, are in Disarmament
                    files, lot 58 D 133, “Panel of Consultants on Disarmament”.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
